The paper discusses the development of a domain-specific language for efficient implementation of rigid body dynamics algorithms in robot controllers and simulations. This topic falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as software engineering (cs.SE) since the paper proposes a language for software development. The paper also mentions the use of facilities available for domain-specific languages (cs.PL) and the need for real-time constraints in high-frequency control loops (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents preliminary results of a proof of concept for generating efficient code (cs.LG).
